# myClawTeam Theming Architecture Plan

## Product Context

myClawTeam is a static Astro landing page for the product positioning "Agent Team for Founders." The next issue batch migrates the existing Tailwind color system from hard-coded palette scales to semantic CSS variable tokens while preserving the current visual design and adding theme switching.

## Module Structure

- `src/styles/global.css`: owns base Tailwind imports, root semantic CSS variables, named theme overrides such as `[data-theme="dark"]`, and base element styles that consume semantic variables.
- `tailwind.config.mjs`: maps semantic Tailwind color names to CSS variables with `rgb(var(--color-...) / <alpha-value>)`; legacy `brand`, `ink`, `signal`, and `surface` scales remain only during migration.
- `src/config/site.ts`: remains the shared product/content config and is the likely home for a default theme value if the implementation chooses config-driven theme selection.
- `src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro`: applies `<html data-theme="...">`, imports global CSS, and continues to own SEO, fonts, and asset links.
- `src/components/sections/*.astro`: migrate section classes from legacy palette utilities to semantic color utilities in grouped batches:
  - `Hero.astro` and `ValueProps.astro`
  - `HowItWorks.astro` and `FeatureHighlights.astro`
  - `FinalCta.astro` and `Footer.astro`
- `README.md`: documents the theme system, theme switching via `data-theme` / `PUBLIC_THEME`, and how to add named themes.
- `docs/production-verification.md`: records which theme was verified after the migration.

## Shared Types and Data

- Keep product copy in `src/config/site.ts`; theming should not duplicate content or introduce client-side state unless required.
- If a theme setting is added to config, keep it as a small string literal value and validate/fallback in the layout so invalid `PUBLIC_THEME` values do not break rendering.
- CSS variables should use RGB triplets, not hex values, so Tailwind opacity modifiers continue to work through `<alpha-value>`.

## Issue Dependencies

- Issue #35 defines the semantic CSS variable contract in `global.css`.
- Issue #36 maps Tailwind semantic color keys to those variables while retaining legacy palette scales during migration.
- Issue #37 adds light/default plus dark theme palettes and sets `data-theme` from config or `PUBLIC_THEME`.
- Issues #38, #39, and #40 migrate all section components to semantic utilities in batches.
- Issue #41 removes the legacy palette scales after all component usage is migrated, greps for remaining legacy class names, and verifies `astro build` plus Playwright smoke tests.
- Issue #42 updates README and production verification docs once the semantic theme system is complete.

## Key Design Decisions

- Preserve current light-theme output first; dark theme support should be additive and should not force layout or copy changes.
- Keep the semantic token names stable and product-agnostic: `primary`, `background`, `surface`, `foreground`, `muted`, `border`, and `accent`.
- Avoid a broken intermediate state by keeping legacy palettes in Tailwind until every component has migrated.
- Prefer CSS-variable theming over runtime JavaScript so the site remains static, fast, and deployable from `dist/`.
- Verify visually relevant changes with the existing build and Playwright smoke workflow before removing legacy scales.
